TextEng: Who are you? What are you doing here?
Text: 넌 누구야? 여기서 뭐 하는 거야?

TextEng: Who you be and what you be doing here?
How can you help me?
How you help me?
Sorry. I'm not talking to a demon. Goodbye.
Text: 미안하지만 악마와는 얘기 안 해. 안녕.

TextEng: Me not talk to demon. Bye!
What do you want from me?
Me hear what you want first.
Tell me more about how you can help me.
Text: 어떻게 날 도와줄 수 있는지 더 말해봐.

TextEng: Me wanting know how you is helping me.
I'd rather not have you help me. Goodbye.
Me not want you is helping me. At all!
<StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> Do I need to sell my soul or something?
Text: <StartCheck>[통찰]</Start> 혹시 영혼을 팔아야 하는 건 아니겠지?

TextEng: Take the talisman. Now, how will you help me?
Text: 부적을 가져가. 이제, 어떻게 날 도와줄 건데?

TextEng: Me gives you talisman. You helping now?
No, I won't give you the talisman you want.
Text: 아니, 네가 원하는 부적은 안 줘.

TextEng: Me not gives you my talisman.
I'd like you to open all of the doors.
Me wants stuck doors opened!
Give me a powerful magical item.
Me wants magic item! Powerful magic item!
Text: 나 마법 아이템 원해! 강력한 마법 아이템!

TextEng: I don't want you to do anything for me.
Me not want you helping me at all!
Fine, I will do this.
Me can do this.
So without those talismans you're trapped here?
Text: 그럼 부적들이 없으면 여기 갇혀 있는 거야?

TextEng: So if you not get jewelry you be trapped here?
Text: 부적 못 받으면 여기 갇혀 있는 거야?

TextEng: I will not do this for you!
If me gets talismans, me is keeping!
Text: 내가 부적 찾으면 나 가질 거야!

TextEng: I have one of your talismans here.
Hey! Me gots you jewelry here now!
Fine, you may help me then,
Me changes mind. You can helps me.
No. I do not wish your aid.
Me not needs you do thing.
How do I know that I can trust you?
Text: 널 믿을 수 있다는 걸 어떻게 알아?

TextEng: Me not thinking me can trust you.
Text: 나 너 믿을 수 없을 것 같아.
